options.markdown:
Total number of rulesets and rules created in MPM


These charts show the total number of rulesets and different types of rules created in Metrics Pipeline Management.

chart.description: Datapoints received and the effective OrgLimit (may be higher than subscription limit)
chart.name: DPM - Limit Utilization

publishLabelOptions.displayName: 3-Datapoints Dropped using metric pipeline management (MPM) rules
publishLabelOptions.label: C

chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.datapointsTotalCount', rollup='rate').scale(60).mean(over='1m').publish(label='A')
F = (E*10).publish(label='F')
C = data('sf.org.numDatapointsDroppedMetricRuleset', rollup='rate').mean(over='1m').scale(60).publish(label='C')
G = data('sf.org.numBillableDatapoints').mean(over='1m').publish(label='G')
D = data('OrgLimits', filter=filter('name', 'dpmLimit'), rollup='latest', extrapolation='last_value').sum(by=['sf_metric']).publish(label='D')
E = data('sf.org.numBillableArchivedDatapoints').publish(label='E', enable=False)
B = data('sf.org.numDatapointsReceived', filter=(not filter('category', '*')), rollup='rate').mean(over='1m').scale(60).publish(label='B', enable=False)

chart.programText:
A = data('sf.org.numBillableArchivedDatapoints', rollup='average', extrapolation='last_value').mean(over='1m').publish(label='A', enable=False)
C = data('sf.org.numBillableDatapoints', rollup='average', extrapolation='last_value').mean(over='1m').publish(label='C', enable=False)
G = (C+E).publish(label='G', enable=False)
E = (9*A).publish(label='E', enable=False)
F = (100*E/G).publish(label='F')
B = data('sf.org.numArchivedDatapointsReceived', rollup='average').publish(label='B', enable=False)
D = data('sf.org.grossArchivedDatapointsReceived', rollup='average').publish(label='D', enable=False)
